<table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0"><tr><td>
	     <table class="mform"  border="0" cellpadding="1" cellspacing="0" width="100%" >
	     <form action="/cgi-bin/mrate.pl" name="f10317059874954">
	     <tr><td id="headerrow" colspan="2" class="mform" valign="top"><a id="sj" href="">RE: Best combo</a> <a id="fs8" href="#post"><img src="/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif" border="0" alt="Reply..." width="17" height="11" /></a>
	     <br clear="all" /><small>Posted @ Tue, Sep 10th 9:14 PM 2002</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform"><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=64677"><span id="Sage">xaanru</span></a><br /><b><span id="Sage">Sage</span></b><br /><span id="notbold">3191 posts<br /><span id="notbold">Score</span>: Excellent [4.78]</td><td valign=top class="mform" width="100%"><p>Well, this post pretty much includes every wrong notion about dual wield that I have ever seen.<br/><br/>Primary and secondary hand delay are not linked. You could have a 40 delay in primary (wurmy), and a 19 delay in secondary (i.e.lammy), and the lammy could swing up to 4 times for each swing cycle of the primary. This would be a successful dual wield, and double attack roll, which is rare, but the bottom line is, a slow primary has NO EFFECT on secondary speed. <br/><br/>The second myth is that Wurmslayer is &quot;too slow&quot; for a ranger. It's not. Its too slow for a Warrior, or the rare (hopefully) Main Tank (MT) ranger. For a ranger acting as a secondary melee, Wurmy is great. The lower speed decreases hate, so you are much less likely to pull aggro off the MT. The ratio on Wurmslayer is so good, that it makes up for the loss of damage bonuses, caused by fewer swings, at least up to lvl 50 or so. <br/><br/>Also, Ironically, if you were to choose the pair of weapons he recommends, in most cases, they should be in the opposite hands from what he suggests. The BA LS is 14/25 when you factor in the magic damage, which is a better ratio than the Centi. It also is faster, meaning the damage bonus applied more frequently. Third, it has a proc, and since primary swings more often, you'll be more likely to proc in primary.<br/><br/>However, if you are gaining aggro to often, you may want to reverse them, just to reduce hate. Although if it happens too much, I'd probably get a new tank, or get your tank some better aggroing weapons.<br/><br/>His next myth is that wurmy is &quot;too much aggro&quot;. Very few weapons creat less aggro than wurmslayer. It is primarily the NUMBER of hits, not the damage that creates aggro. Lammy would outtaunt wurmy every time. And faster weapons, as he recommends, will get you dead.<br/><br/>BTW, the only problem with Wurmslayer/lammy combo is that lammy has a weak ratio for secondary. JBoM, CLS, and a number of other weapons will cause more damage in secondary. Wurmslayer is an IDEAL weapon for rangers, as long as your stamina is over 100.</p>&nbsp;<br /></td></tr>
